<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8eea1408-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s297"><num value="297">§ 297.</num><heading> Acquisition of property by lease</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The authority granted to acquire sites and buildings by purchase or otherwise shall include authority to acquire leaseholds.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8eea1409-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/act/1926-05-07/ch250/s6">May 7, 1926, ch. 250, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/405">44 Stat. 405</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1952-06-19/ch446/s4">June 19, 1952, ch. 446, § 4</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/66/140">66 Stat. 140</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/95/105/tI/s106/b">Pub. L. 95–105, title I, § 106(b)</ref>, <date date="1977-08-17">Aug. 17, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/845">91 Stat. 845</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8eea140a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8eea140b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id8eea140c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1977—<ref href="/us/pl/95/105">Pub. L. 95–105</ref> struck out “of not less than ten years” after “acquire leaseholds”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1952—Act <date date="1952-06-19">June 19, 1952</date>, provided for leaseholds of not less than 10 years.</p>
</note>
</notes>
